Aim
To design and implement a temperature control system using IoT.
Requirements
• ESP32
• DHT11/DHT22 Sensor
• Fan/LED
• Blynk App
• WiFi Connection
Procedure
Step 1: Circuit Connection
1. Open Wokwi/Tinkercad or use ESP32 hardware.
2. Connect DHT sensor to ESP32.
3. Connect fan/LED to GPIO pin.
Step 2: Blynk Setup
1. Install Blynk IoT application.
2. Create a new template.
3. Copy the Authentication Token.
Step 3: Configure Datastream
1. Create Virtual Pin V0.
2. Add monitoring widget in dashboard.
Step 4: Arduino Programming
1. Open Arduino IDE.
2. Install DHT and Blynk libraries.
3. Write and upload the program.
Step 5: Execution
1. Start the simulation.
2. Monitor temperature values.
3. Observe automatic fan/LED control.
Result
Thus, the temperature control system using IoT was implemented successfully.
